# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: per-folder .gitignore usage tips
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# - If you keep frontend and backend as separate folders, you can add stricter .gitignore files inside:
#   /frontend/.gitignore  (Node-specific)
#   /backend/.gitignore   (Python-specific)
#   /contracts/.gitignore (Hardhat/Truffle-specific)
#
# - Keep production config (e.g. production env files) out of the repo and store in your deployment secrets manager.
